WEBVTT

00:00.166 --> 00:02.041
[Deena] Previously
on What About Brian:

00:02.041 --> 00:05.375
- Talk to me.
- Carrie's deaf.
She lost her hearing.

00:05.375 --> 00:08.834
- I would do the surgery.
- Then that's what we should do.

00:08.834 --> 00:12.542
All you need to know
about my life is that
you're not a part of it.

00:12.542 --> 00:15.667
It's a summons.
He's suing you?!

00:15.667 --> 00:17.709
Heather and I,
we had an arrangement.

00:17.709 --> 00:20.166
You don't know your wife
as well as you thought.

00:20.166 --> 00:25.000
I was thinking... maybe
you'd want to move in, with me.

00:28.667 --> 00:30.875
- [Bridget] Who ate my Kashi?
- [Dave] Brian.

00:30.875 --> 00:32.375
I don't eat Kashi.

00:32.375 --> 00:34.542
Doesn't matter.
There's no milk.

00:34.542 --> 00:37.709
- Bridget's fault.
- I don't get milk.
I don't even live here.

00:37.709 --> 00:40.625
- I'm just staying here.
- I'm just spending the night.

00:40.625 --> 00:44.417
- I thought you were moving in.
- No, Brian's moving
into my place.

00:44.417 --> 00:45.583
[inaudible] No way.

00:45.583 --> 00:48.417
This is Brian's place.
He should buy the milk.

00:48.417 --> 00:51.709
- Who wants the sports page?
- [both] I do.

00:51.709 --> 00:54.709
Speaking of papers, your dad
gave me stuff to give you.

00:54.709 --> 00:57.834
- Some, uh,
papers for you to sign.
- What papers?

00:57.834 --> 01:01.917
- Selling his house in Big Bear.
- He can't do that.
Why's he doing that?

01:01.917 --> 01:04.000
Already done. Buyers
are moving in in two weeks.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.125
- Oh, man.
- That's terrible.

01:06.125 --> 01:07.750
We didn't get
to say good-bye.

01:07.750 --> 01:10.458
No. Remember when
we'd go up there?

01:10.458 --> 01:13.875
Friday night, pack up all
our stuff, spend the weekend?

01:13.875 --> 01:16.500
You know, we should
go up there. This weekend.

01:16.500 --> 01:19.250
- Who's we?
- You're right. Everybody.

01:19.250 --> 01:21.709
Adam, Nic, Jimmy, Ivy.
The whole gang.

01:21.709 --> 01:23.375
- Deena too?
- Yeah, Deena too.

01:23.375 --> 01:26.834
I'll stop by the house on my way
to work. That's a great idea.

01:27.625 --> 01:29.875
Oh, work. We should go.

01:29.875 --> 01:34.417
So you and me and all
of your friends are gonna get
together for the weekend?

01:34.417 --> 01:36.917
It'll be practice
for when we move in together.

01:36.917 --> 01:40.333
- Your friends
are moving into my place?
- You're moving into mine.

01:40.333 --> 01:42.959
- I don't think so.
- Whatever.

01:42.959 --> 01:45.125
[doorbell chimes]

01:45.125 --> 01:47.500
- [cell phone rings]
- Somebody get the door.

01:47.500 --> 01:50.166
- [Larissa] I want to!
- [Geneva] You got it last time!

01:50.166 --> 01:54.583
- Hello.
Yeah, this is Deena Greco.
- [girls] Daddy! Daddy!

01:54.583 --> 01:57.834
- When do we have to decide by?
- What are you doing here?

01:57.834 --> 02:01.750
- I'm gonna take you
to the mountains.
- [girls cheering]

02:01.750 --> 02:04.083
Mommy's on the phone.
We got to be quiet.

02:04.083 --> 02:07.500
I guess we will call you
first thing Monday morning then.

02:07.500 --> 02:09.458
No, thank you. Bye.

02:09.458 --> 02:13.041
- Who's that?
- It was the surgeon's office.

02:13.041 --> 02:17.041
They had a cancellation
and they can do Carrie's
surgery next Friday.

02:17.041 --> 02:19.083
So... does it...

02:19.083 --> 02:23.000
- Daddy's taking us
to the mountains!
- [Deena] Wow.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.834
Yeah, I was thinking
of taking you guys up
to Brian's dad's place,

02:26.834 --> 02:30.166
- but we probably should...
- Maybe another weekend, girls.

02:30.166 --> 02:33.375
- [both groan]
- We said we were
gonna take them there.

02:33.375 --> 02:36.333
This will be great for us.
We'll get out of town.

02:36.333 --> 02:39.750
The whole gang's going.
Maybe get a little perspective.

02:39.750 --> 02:43.166
We'll go up the mountain,
make a decision,
come down like Moses.

02:43.166 --> 02:46.583
- Please, Mommy.
- Come on. Please, Mommy.

02:46.583 --> 02:49.875
- Oh, OK! OK! OK.
- [all cheering]

02:51.291 --> 02:53.208
Are these boots OK
for the mountains?

02:54.250 --> 02:56.041
Don't you have
any hiking boots?

02:56.041 --> 02:58.083
I don't really do nature.

02:58.083 --> 03:00.333
- You can use Nic's.
- Isn't she coming?

03:00.333 --> 03:03.625
Bella's too little and all those
people. Especially the kids.

03:03.625 --> 03:05.625
Kids are walking germ factories.

03:05.625 --> 03:09.375
If she's not going, I'm not.
She's the only one
that likes me.

03:09.375 --> 03:13.542
- Dave likes you.
Jimmy likes you.
- Women. Women don't like me.

03:13.542 --> 03:16.291
- That's ridiculous.
- No, I'm serious.

03:16.291 --> 03:19.709
I grew up with three brothers.
I don't know how
to talk to women.

03:19.709 --> 03:21.875
"He's so cute."
"I like your earrings."

03:21.875 --> 03:25.291
- I'm not good at that.
- These girls like you.

03:25.291 --> 03:29.250
Or at least they will
after this weekend.
I'll make sure of it.

03:32.500 --> 03:34.500
I have something for you.

03:38.667 --> 03:40.750
A key to my place.

03:42.583 --> 03:46.834
[laughs] Oh... OK, thanks.

03:47.959 --> 03:50.166
Brian, why can't
we figure this out?

03:50.166 --> 03:52.917
Whose place
we're moving into.

03:55.166 --> 03:56.750
You know why.

03:56.750 --> 04:00.583
I think I do, but I want
to hear what you think.

04:00.583 --> 04:03.417
Neither one of us
wants to give up our place.

04:03.417 --> 04:06.500
Give up the security of it.

04:06.500 --> 04:08.917
You know, because
what if it doesn't work out?

04:10.542 --> 04:12.917
What if we break up...

04:12.917 --> 04:17.625
...and then we gave up
our home for... nothing.

04:17.625 --> 04:22.125
Well, when you put it like that,
it's a wonder anyone
ever gets together.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.709
I can't go with you
to the mountains this weekend.

04:26.709 --> 04:29.458
- Why not? You got to come.
- I'm working.

04:29.458 --> 04:32.417
- You can study up there.
- Not studying.

04:32.417 --> 04:34.625
I'm picking up
extra shifts at the club.

04:34.625 --> 04:37.875
Five or six Saturdays until I
make enough to pay Schmitty.

04:37.875 --> 04:40.125
And he'll drop the suit.

04:43.542 --> 04:45.458
Do you actually think
I'd be OK with this?

04:45.458 --> 04:51.083
- No. I knew you wouldn't, but..
- I'll pay Schmitty the money.

04:51.083 --> 04:56.333
Heather, don't miss out on this
weekend because of him. Please?

04:56.333 --> 04:59.417
We used to go up all the time.
All the friends together.

04:59.417 --> 05:02.458
- Marjorie too?
- Yeah, she used to go up.

05:02.458 --> 05:05.792
- Is she gonna be there?
- No. No, of course not.

05:05.792 --> 05:08.667
And even if she were,
I'd still want you to go.

05:08.667 --> 05:12.000
Adam, I can't make it
through a birthday party.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.291
I'm not ready to go
on vacation with her.

05:15.291 --> 05:17.667
Yeah. OK. Well, don't come.

05:20.333 --> 05:24.333
You know, maybe it's better
if we have some time apart.

05:27.125 --> 05:29.625
- Adam...
- I have to pack.

05:29.625 --> 05:30.750
[door slams]

05:31.750 --> 05:33.000
[soft rock plays]

05:33.000 --> 05:34.709
♪ All my life ♪

05:34.709 --> 05:37.500
♪ I'm trying
to break this spell ♪

05:37.500 --> 05:41.375
♪ By drinking the water
from the bottom of the well ♪

05:41.375 --> 05:44.375
Marjorie. Hi.

05:44.375 --> 05:46.208
I was hoping we could talk.

05:46.208 --> 05:48.667
- About what?
- About Adam.

05:51.625 --> 05:56.625
♪ Nobody knows ♪♪

05:56.625 --> 05:58.834
[♪ Low Stars: Calling All
Friends]

05:58.834 --> 06:03.041
♪ Calling all friends and
people I met on the way down ♪

06:03.041 --> 06:08.959
♪ Calling all friends
and people I don't even know ♪

06:08.959 --> 06:10.792
♪ Calling on high ♪

06:10.792 --> 06:15.041
♪ I want to believe
there's a way now ♪

06:15.041 --> 06:20.500
♪ I'm too tired to pretend
I don't wanna be alone ♪

06:20.500 --> 06:23.417
♪ I'm calling all friends ♪♪

06:39.041 --> 06:43.083
Wow, this is amazing.

06:43.083 --> 06:44.917
There's a key
around here somewhere.

06:44.917 --> 06:47.959
I wish we were by ourselves.
We could do it in every room.

06:47.959 --> 06:50.959
- We can still do that.
- We're not
gonna be that couple.

06:50.959 --> 06:53.041
- What couple?
- The sex couple.

06:53.041 --> 06:55.959
The ones sneaking off to do it
or talking about it

06:55.959 --> 06:58.458
or doing it so loudly
everyone can hear.

06:58.458 --> 07:00.458
The grabber takes
the best room.

07:00.458 --> 07:03.125
The camp counselor
overschedules everything.

07:03.125 --> 07:07.750
There's the one who's too
competitive and the girlfriend
who ends up in tears.

07:07.750 --> 07:12.583
Come on. I'm sure we
can knock off a few rooms
before anyone gets here.

07:12.583 --> 07:17.083
Mmm. [giggles] Wow!

07:17.083 --> 07:18.166
Does Adam know?

07:19.417 --> 07:21.291
About this meeting
we're having?

07:21.291 --> 07:23.917
No. He's out of town
at Brian's cabin.

07:23.917 --> 07:26.250
It's his dad's.
I love that place.

07:26.250 --> 07:29.041
What is your
intention exactly
towards my husband?

07:29.041 --> 07:30.625
I don't have any intention.

07:30.625 --> 07:32.959
Because Adam and I are married.
We're happy.

07:32.959 --> 07:35.500
If you came back to
get back together with him...

07:35.500 --> 07:39.667
I did not come back here for
Adam. I came back for myself.

07:39.667 --> 07:42.750
- You don't have
feelings for him?
- Of course I do.

07:43.667 --> 07:46.041
We have a history.

07:46.041 --> 07:49.166
I was with Adam for two years.
You've known him for a month.

07:49.166 --> 07:51.834
But I never hurt him.

07:51.834 --> 07:54.166
You screwed him. I'm not
gonna let it happen again.

07:54.166 --> 07:55.834
I'm not doing anything.

07:55.834 --> 07:59.917
It is what it is.
If Adam has feelings for me,
you can't change that.

07:59.917 --> 08:01.792
- You can't control him.
- I'm his wife.

08:01.792 --> 08:03.458
Any more than I can.

08:06.750 --> 08:11.250
- Oh, look at the lake!
- [giggles]

08:11.250 --> 08:13.458
Uh, girls?
Please don't jump on the couch.

08:13.458 --> 08:15.834
Come on, Larissa.
Let's go look upstairs.

08:15.834 --> 08:18.583
- [Adam] Hey, everybody!
- Hey, what's up, buddy?

08:18.583 --> 08:22.041
- Where's Heather?
- She couldn't make it, honey.

08:22.041 --> 08:25.125
How will he know you'd be ready
to do the surgery in a week?

08:25.125 --> 08:29.291
Doesn't he have to get to know
her and do tests on her and...

08:29.291 --> 08:32.542
OK. Well, would you please call
me after you talk to him?

08:32.542 --> 08:35.125
- Thanks, honey. Bye.
- [phone beeps off]

08:35.125 --> 08:36.959
Who was that?

08:36.959 --> 08:41.083
Um, actually, it was...
it was Marjorie.

08:43.208 --> 08:47.000
Mmm. How are you holding up?
You know, with Carrie?

08:47.000 --> 08:49.875
I'm OK. Thanks.

08:49.875 --> 08:52.875
Talking to Marjorie
really calms me down.

08:52.875 --> 08:56.041
She's just so clear and smart.

08:56.041 --> 08:58.875
Well, it is nice having
a doctor around, you know?

08:58.875 --> 09:03.709
One time I thought I had
appendicitis and it turned out
to be really bad gas.

09:03.709 --> 09:05.500
It was like
this shooting pain.

09:05.500 --> 09:08.583
Another time I had
this burning sensation...

09:08.583 --> 09:12.667
OK, yeah. Speaking of that...
did you bring the sausage?

09:12.667 --> 09:15.917
[Dave] Listen up. First activity
of the day is gonna be fishing.

09:15.917 --> 09:17.500
- [guys] Yeah!
- Yeah!

09:17.500 --> 09:20.750
The van leaves in 30 minutes,
and novices are welcome.

09:20.750 --> 09:25.083
- What's a novice?
- A novice is someone who's
never gone fishing before.

09:25.083 --> 09:27.583
- Wanna go fishing
with your dad?
- I'm scared.

09:27.583 --> 09:31.041
- Why?
- I don't wanna turn out
like Mr. Jeremy Fisher.

09:31.041 --> 09:33.417
Who's Jeremy Fisher?

09:33.417 --> 09:37.000
He's this salamander who
almost gets eaten by a trout.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.500
- My people!
- [all] Hey!

09:39.500 --> 09:41.417
- Where you guys been?
- You're late.

09:41.417 --> 09:44.709
- We got pulled over.
- You're kidding me?
For speeding?

09:44.709 --> 09:47.208
Not really.
It was more like for weaving.

09:47.208 --> 09:49.542
No, it was more
of a bob than a weave.

09:49.542 --> 09:52.125
Jimmy getting
something-something on the 215?

09:52.125 --> 09:55.291
- What's a something-something?
- It's nothing-nothing.

09:55.291 --> 09:57.458
Sex couple.

10:00.709 --> 10:03.458
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:04.291 --> 10:06.959
Wow...

10:06.959 --> 10:09.291
...there's a lot
of memories in this house.

10:09.291 --> 10:10.875
Yeah.

10:10.875 --> 10:14.291
Did you ask me to marry you
on the deck or down by the lake?

10:14.291 --> 10:17.875
[laughs] Oh, I think it
was down by the lake.

10:17.875 --> 10:19.458
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

10:19.458 --> 10:22.625
You remember I was
going back and forth

10:22.625 --> 10:25.333
whether or not I
should ask you up here.

10:25.333 --> 10:29.250
And right before we left,
I pulled you down there,
asked you.

10:29.250 --> 10:32.750
Everybody was waiting
in their cars,
knowing what I was doing.

10:35.250 --> 10:39.417
So is that what you're
doing now, about the surgery?

10:39.417 --> 10:42.166
Just kind of
going back and forth?

10:42.166 --> 10:45.125
- Yeah, sort of.
- Well, let's talk about it.

10:46.083 --> 10:47.417
Kind of going fishing.

10:47.417 --> 10:49.667
Dave, we came up here
to discuss this.

10:49.667 --> 10:52.917
It's Saturday. We have
till Monday. I need
some time to think.

10:52.917 --> 10:54.750
You have had
24 hours to think.

10:54.750 --> 10:56.291
Why are you rushing me?

10:56.291 --> 10:58.667
You push and push.
You're always rushing me.

10:58.667 --> 11:00.333
Why put it off, you know?

11:00.333 --> 11:03.667
I'm not. This is my process.
This is what I do.

11:03.667 --> 11:06.291
Your process
doesn't mesh with my process.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.458
Really, Deen?

11:07.458 --> 11:08.875
- Yeah.
- You think?

11:08.875 --> 11:11.542
I didn't come to make
sandwiches, sit on the beach.

11:11.542 --> 11:14.291
I came here to make a decision.
And I wanna make it now.

11:14.291 --> 11:17.000
Not tomorrow,
not on the ride home!

11:17.000 --> 11:20.458
I promise you we're gonna make
a decision this weekend, Deena!

11:20.458 --> 11:22.125
[sighs]

11:27.500 --> 11:29.709
Who's ready to have some fun?

11:34.000 --> 11:36.041
I can't believe
she took the best room.

11:36.041 --> 11:38.542
Oh, I can.
She didn't bring anything.

11:38.542 --> 11:41.667
Not a bottle of wine. Not even
a packet of microwave popcorn.

11:41.667 --> 11:45.542
- Brian brought stuff.
- Of course.
He's nice. He's thoughtful.

11:45.542 --> 11:48.041
She just knows a good thing
when she sees it.

11:50.750 --> 11:53.208
Guys, what are you doing
while we go fishing?

11:53.208 --> 11:55.709
We thought we'd do
some hunting and gathering.

11:55.709 --> 11:59.041
- Nuts, berries.
Maybe sit by the lake.
- [Ivy laughs]

11:59.041 --> 12:00.875
Would you ask Bridget
to join you?

12:00.875 --> 12:03.583
She's got this crazy idea
you guys don't like her.

12:03.583 --> 12:05.041
What? No, it's nutty.

12:05.041 --> 12:08.000
I will totally invite her.
I love that girl.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.917
- All right. Thanks.
- You bet.

12:09.917 --> 12:13.166
- [rock music plays]
- ♪ She's a wicked girl ♪

12:13.166 --> 12:16.083
♪ Worst in all the world ♪

12:16.083 --> 12:20.208
♪ A mystery lies ♪

12:20.208 --> 12:24.166
- That girl must die.
- Mommy, why don't you exercise?

12:24.166 --> 12:26.250
That's because
Mommy's on vacation.

12:26.250 --> 12:27.834
Oh.

12:28.917 --> 12:30.250
[Adam] Wow.

12:30.250 --> 12:32.667
[Dave] Give me that. Give me.

12:35.542 --> 12:38.250
[Dave] Wow, wow, wow. [exhales]

12:38.250 --> 12:39.542
- Hey, Bri.
- Yeah.

12:39.542 --> 12:41.208
Is she as flexible in bed?

12:41.208 --> 12:43.625
[Jimmy and Adam laugh]

12:46.834 --> 12:48.750
Give me those.

12:51.250 --> 12:54.417
[Brian] God, she is gorgeous.

12:54.417 --> 12:57.750
- Is she really mine?
- Unfortunately.
Pass the binoculars.

12:57.750 --> 13:01.291
- I can't move in
to her apartment.
- [guys mumbling]

13:01.291 --> 13:04.291
If I move into her place,
it's over. I'll cease
to be Brian.

13:04.291 --> 13:07.458
We'll have our picture
on some bus bench together,

13:07.458 --> 13:09.875
"Your Westside
real estate professionals."

13:09.875 --> 13:12.166
I'll come home from work
with potpourri

13:12.166 --> 13:16.041
and the white wine and the
loofa exfoliating scrubbers.

13:16.041 --> 13:18.250
Put a dress on me
and call me Lola.

13:18.250 --> 13:20.000
It's great, a woman's touch.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.667
Says the man sleeping
on my couch for ten weeks.

13:22.667 --> 13:26.667
How can you defend
the joys of couplehood?
You're getting a divorce.

13:26.667 --> 13:29.250
And you?
Your wife isn't even here.

13:29.250 --> 13:30.834
You're right, Bri. We suck.

13:30.834 --> 13:33.959
I'm not here alone by choice.
I wanted to be with her.

13:33.959 --> 13:35.917
Could've stayed home.

13:35.917 --> 13:38.542
No. I wanted to come here.
I got some stuff to figure out.

13:38.542 --> 13:42.166
We all do. I got the moving-in
thing, Dave's got the surgery.

13:42.166 --> 13:45.083
Me and Ivy got to decide
whether to get a cat or a dog.

13:45.083 --> 13:46.667
[all] Dog.

13:46.667 --> 13:50.208
Definitely. I don't know
what that woman's problem is.

13:50.208 --> 13:51.959
Dude, you're so getting a cat.

13:51.959 --> 13:54.834
- Am not.
It's my house, I'm getting...
- [Adam meows]

13:57.875 --> 14:02.208
"Mr. Jeremy Fisher would have
been eaten, if not for his
yellow mackintosh

14:02.208 --> 14:05.125
which the fish found distasteful
and spit him out."

14:05.125 --> 14:07.542
If you like this,
you'd love Jaws.

14:07.542 --> 14:09.375
What's Jaws?

14:09.375 --> 14:13.208
It's about a big shark
that likes to eat little girls
on vacation.

14:13.208 --> 14:14.959
Hey! Do not tell
her about Jaws!

14:14.959 --> 14:17.709
I am going to attack Kamchatka.

14:17.709 --> 14:21.458
[Bridget] The water pressure
is fantastic here.

14:21.458 --> 14:24.208
[clears throat]
Here I am, reporting for duty!

14:24.208 --> 14:26.875
A cat is easier to take
care of if you go out of town.

14:26.875 --> 14:28.417
- Cats are smarter.
- Mm-hmm.

14:28.417 --> 14:31.792
Hey, what are you doing?
I thought I was
on the chart for dinner.

14:31.792 --> 14:35.417
Oh, no, Bridge. I think Ivy and
I have it all under control.

14:35.417 --> 14:40.709
Yeah. I mean, you can help
the guys with the dishes after.

14:40.709 --> 14:42.625
- There you go. Yeah, good idea.
- OK.

14:42.625 --> 14:47.542
- Oh, hey. Deena votes cat.
- So? All the guys vote dog.

14:47.542 --> 14:50.750
- OK, Bridget? Bridget?
- Hmm?

14:50.750 --> 14:54.583
Um, which is the better pet,
a cat or a dog?

14:56.083 --> 14:58.667
Um... A dog.

14:58.667 --> 15:01.834
- [Jimmy] Oh!
- I'm sorry.
It's my honest opinion.

15:01.834 --> 15:03.667
- [laughs loudly]
- I'm a dog person.

15:03.667 --> 15:06.166
- [Ivy] Hey, that's cool.
- Yeah.

15:08.083 --> 15:12.333
- [phone rings]
- Hello.

15:13.291 --> 15:15.333
Oh, hi, Marjorie.
Yeah, I'm sorry.

15:15.333 --> 15:18.875
I didn't recognize your voice.
Yeah. No, it's beautiful.

15:18.875 --> 15:23.709
You know, it's great. The lake
and we got fires and games.

15:23.709 --> 15:26.375
You talk to Deena so much
you might as well be here.

15:26.375 --> 15:29.166
I know. I know, here she is.

15:30.875 --> 15:35.375
Hi. Yeah. Oh, Carrie?
No, she's doing great.

15:35.375 --> 15:37.709
Yeah, she's...

15:37.709 --> 15:40.959
Honey? Listen,
let me call you back, OK?

15:40.959 --> 15:42.625
[soft acoustic rock plays]

15:42.625 --> 15:46.041
♪ If tonight
was not a crooked trail ♪

15:46.041 --> 15:50.834
♪ If tomorrow
wasn't such a long time ♪

15:52.583 --> 15:57.291
♪ Then lonesome would mean
nothing to me at all ♪

15:58.792 --> 16:00.834
You see that?

16:00.834 --> 16:03.667
There's nothing
to be afraid of

16:03.667 --> 16:09.291
because the fish are really
little and you are really big.

16:09.291 --> 16:12.291
Much bigger
than Mr. Jeremy Fisher.

16:12.291 --> 16:15.625
- [Geneva] Yeah.
- Yeah. Here,
push that button down.

16:15.625 --> 16:20.166
Give it a flick of your wrist
right into the water.
You're a natural, my sweet.

16:20.166 --> 16:24.792
Look. You're fishing.
You're really, really fishing.

16:24.792 --> 16:28.166
Yeah, it's easy!
Now all I need is a fly.

16:28.166 --> 16:31.500
- No, a worm.
- Eww.

16:31.500 --> 16:33.750
Worms are slimy.

16:33.750 --> 16:38.000
♪ I can't speak the sounds
that show no pain ♪

16:38.000 --> 16:44.041
♪ I can't hear
the echo of my footsteps ♪

16:44.041 --> 16:49.083
♪ Or remember
the sound of my own name ♪

16:52.083 --> 16:55.125
- [Carrie] Mmm.
- How you doing?

16:55.125 --> 16:59.875
♪ Yes and only
if he was lying by me ♪

16:59.875 --> 17:04.792
♪ Would I lie in my bed ♪

17:04.792 --> 17:07.125
♪ Once again ♪♪

17:08.333 --> 17:10.333
[sigh] The knife
is faced the wrong way.

17:10.333 --> 17:12.458
It is not turned
the wrong way.

17:12.458 --> 17:16.792
We've had this argument
since we were ten and our moms
made us set the table.

17:16.792 --> 17:19.500
- Hey, do you want some wine?
- No, no, no.

17:19.500 --> 17:21.917
No white for Adam, right?
He's red only.

17:21.917 --> 17:25.083
- Does it give him a headache?
- Blinding headaches.

17:25.083 --> 17:27.750
No, like, "I've got a tumor"
headaches.

17:27.750 --> 17:30.041
Up here once,
we got this Two-Buck Chuck.

17:30.041 --> 17:33.750
We had to take him to the
hospital. He thought he was
having an aneurysm.

17:33.750 --> 17:35.834
It was snowing,
we didn't have chains.

17:35.834 --> 17:38.041
Right. And he kept saying,
"I see spots."

17:38.041 --> 17:41.875
- I was!
I was seeing white spots!
- It was snowing!

17:41.875 --> 17:45.709
Well, thank God you started
dating a doctor after that.

17:47.125 --> 17:49.792
- You guys ready to eat?
- Yeah. Ready to eat.

17:51.291 --> 17:53.709
- You guys OK?
- Yeah.

17:55.625 --> 17:57.542
It's the Carrie thing?

17:57.542 --> 18:00.125
This is a little
difficult right now.

18:00.125 --> 18:03.917
Yeah. Come here.
Come here. You know what?

18:03.917 --> 18:07.625
You're gonna make
the right decision because
you're great parents.

18:07.625 --> 18:10.625
I only wish you were my parents.

18:10.625 --> 18:12.333
You'll be my dad?

18:12.333 --> 18:15.166
- Yeah, you just want me
to tuck you in.
- Of course I do.

18:15.166 --> 18:17.041
At the cabin you
gotta get tucked in.

18:17.041 --> 18:19.917
[rock music plays on stereo]

18:19.917 --> 18:23.625
What year was this?
1986 or something?

18:23.625 --> 18:26.583
Come on, Bridget.
Let's go dance.

18:26.583 --> 18:30.291
No, no. Come on, baby.
This is white folks' music.

18:30.291 --> 18:34.792
Look, next you know you're
playing Bruce Springsteen.
Flock of Seagulls.

18:34.792 --> 18:37.458
Deen, you played
this record nonstop for months.

18:37.458 --> 18:40.750
- I don't really feel like it.
- That's why you need it,
come on!

18:40.750 --> 18:43.125
Whoa!

18:43.125 --> 18:46.542
♪ Broken at the bitter end ♪

18:46.542 --> 18:48.000
♪ Wasted ♪

18:48.000 --> 18:50.792
- [doorbell]
- We expecting someone?

18:50.792 --> 18:53.500
- A mysterious visitor.
- Ooh!

18:53.500 --> 18:56.834
- Every good weekend needs that.
- Maybe Nic decided to show up.

18:56.834 --> 19:00.959
Hey, guys!
Look, Marjorie's here.

19:00.959 --> 19:03.333
- Hi!
- Hey!

19:18.917 --> 19:23.667
Did you mean it when
you said that I should come?
On the phone?

19:23.667 --> 19:25.667
I didn't actually
think you'd do it.

19:27.458 --> 19:29.500
So maybe this is a mistake?

19:29.500 --> 19:33.834
No. No, no. I didn't... No.

19:38.542 --> 19:40.542
Heather came to see me.

19:41.709 --> 19:44.625
What? What for?

19:44.625 --> 19:47.291
She told me to stay
away from you, basically.

19:50.375 --> 19:51.792
Oh, God.

19:51.792 --> 19:55.500
She married you, I didn't.
It's her prerogative.

19:55.500 --> 19:58.792
But when we talked
on the phone, I just...

20:00.709 --> 20:02.875
I wanted to be here.

20:02.875 --> 20:05.542
I mean, I wanted to
be up here with everyone.

20:07.125 --> 20:08.709
Do I have to give that up?

20:09.917 --> 20:11.667
I hope not.

20:12.500 --> 20:14.250
Well, that's what I decided.

20:20.500 --> 20:24.166
I'm not gonna stay away from you
unless you tell me to stay away.

20:28.917 --> 20:31.208
So do you want me
to stay away?

20:35.166 --> 20:36.417
No.

20:38.500 --> 20:42.083
[sighs] No, I don't.

20:42.083 --> 20:46.667
I mean, besides, it's weird
up here without you.

20:46.667 --> 20:48.583
Everything reminds
me of you.

20:50.291 --> 20:52.125
I've been thinking
about you too.

20:52.125 --> 20:54.125
Oh, yeah?

20:54.125 --> 20:56.375
Well,
we're playing the name game.

20:56.375 --> 20:59.250
You want to be my partner?
It's either you or Larissa.

20:59.250 --> 21:01.750
Well, good. You guys
are intellectual equals.

21:01.750 --> 21:03.291
That's funny.

21:03.291 --> 21:05.625
- Russian leader, splotch.
- Mikhail Gorbachev.

21:05.625 --> 21:07.125
- Unibrow.
- Frida Kahlo.

21:07.125 --> 21:09.125
- Come on.
- Baseball player who...

21:09.125 --> 21:11.291
- Roberto Clemente!
- Margaritaville.

21:11.291 --> 21:12.959
- Jimmy Buffet.
- Come on.

21:12.959 --> 21:14.959
She was in
Planet of the Apes.

21:14.959 --> 21:17.291
- I don't know.
- He's never going to get it.

21:17.291 --> 21:19.375
- My best friend in high school.
- Kim.

21:19.375 --> 21:21.917
Yeah. And your
favorite shade of green.

21:21.917 --> 21:23.750
- Hunter. Kim Hunter.
- Yes!

21:23.750 --> 21:26.041
- You're not gonna get this one.
- Come on!

21:26.041 --> 21:29.625
I wrote it to stump other
people, and now it's back
to bite me in the ass.

21:29.625 --> 21:30.875
Just try me. Do it!

21:30.875 --> 21:32.500
OK, it's the guy

21:32.500 --> 21:33.959
who sings
The Piña Colada Song.

21:33.959 --> 21:35.917
The Piña Colada Song.

21:37.000 --> 21:38.834
It's...

21:38.834 --> 21:40.750
At least three people
have to know it!

21:40.750 --> 21:42.792
No, I know it. I know it.

21:42.792 --> 21:47.458
OK. You and Bridget will be
happy with your dog
and crappy music tastes.

21:47.458 --> 21:51.291
Woman! Focus on me!
Every time we've been in
a beach bar, playing in the...

21:51.291 --> 21:53.250
- Rupert Holmes?
- I love you so much!

21:53.250 --> 21:55.625
- I love you too!
- OK, what's the score?

21:55.625 --> 21:59.500
Dave and Deena
are winning with 62.

21:59.500 --> 22:02.792
- [cheers] That's right!
- And wait. Check this out.

22:02.792 --> 22:05.834
You guys are bringing up
the rear with, wait for it...

22:05.834 --> 22:07.500
- ...a 15.
- Yeah!

22:07.500 --> 22:11.125
Dave and Deena got 15 in one
minute. This is our third try.

22:11.125 --> 22:16.208
- Four, three, two, one. Go!
- Oh, God.
OK, focus and concentrate.

22:16.208 --> 22:19.208
Easy. Famous woman
that wrote Pride and Prejudice.

22:19.208 --> 22:22.667
- Oh, yeah. Her.
- Early 1800s. England.

22:22.667 --> 22:25.709
- Emily Dickinson.
- Emily Dickinson is American.

22:25.709 --> 22:29.208
- The one in all the movies.
- Sense and Sensibility.

22:29.208 --> 22:32.542
- Yeah, I know. But come on.
- Emma. Clueless.

22:32.542 --> 22:35.542
She wrote a novel where
she was the maid
and then Mr. Darcy

22:35.542 --> 22:38.166
or whoever came in
and married her after all...

22:38.166 --> 22:41.041
- Harriet Beecher Stowe.
- How can you not know this?

22:41.041 --> 22:43.458
- Harriet Beecher Stowe?
- Oh, give me a clue!

22:43.458 --> 22:45.667
- Last name is a city in Texas.
- Houston.

22:45.667 --> 22:48.041
No! Her first name
is like blank Doe!

22:48.041 --> 22:49.709
No, I know. But, come on.

22:49.709 --> 22:54.041
OK. Emma. Clueless.
Mansfield Park! Mansfield Park!

22:54.041 --> 22:56.417
- And time!
- God!

22:56.417 --> 22:59.834
- [group] Ooh!
- [slaps leg] I'm sorry, Bridge.

22:59.834 --> 23:04.375
We're losers! We suck as a team!
No wonder we can't
figure where to live.

23:04.375 --> 23:06.041
I think it's time for a break.

23:06.041 --> 23:08.667
Pee break. Checking on
kids break. Drinks break.

23:08.667 --> 23:10.375
- Want to come with me?
- OK.

23:10.375 --> 23:13.542
- [Dave] What do you need,
buddy?
- [Marjorie] Wait, wait, wait.

23:13.542 --> 23:16.291
- I'll go get you a drink,
all right?
- Yeah.

23:26.417 --> 23:27.875
- [whispers] Hey.
- Hey.

23:27.875 --> 23:30.417
- They sleeping?
- Yeah, like babies.

23:30.417 --> 23:33.750
I don't know how with Bridget
screeching, "Mansfield Park!"

23:33.750 --> 23:36.208
Oh, what's up with that?

23:36.208 --> 23:38.583
- We're killing.
- Yeah. Well,

23:38.583 --> 23:40.583
- we definitely still got it.
- Yeah.

23:40.583 --> 23:42.291
We totally got it.

23:42.291 --> 23:44.834
I watched you
with the girls today.

23:46.667 --> 23:51.333
You're so good with them.
Teaching them how to fish.

23:52.667 --> 23:55.291
[sighs] Geneva's just like you.

23:55.291 --> 23:56.792
What do you mean?

23:56.792 --> 24:00.500
You know, the whole
process thing, you know?

24:00.500 --> 24:03.834
She sort of waits and watches.

24:03.834 --> 24:05.625
Like hovers, you know?

24:05.625 --> 24:08.333
Worries about it and then,

24:08.333 --> 24:10.667
if you don't push her,
she gets around to it,

24:10.667 --> 24:14.083
- in her own time.
- She does.

24:14.083 --> 24:18.500
And I see those two beauties
together, Geneva and Larissa,

24:18.500 --> 24:22.333
how close they are. Man.

24:24.041 --> 24:26.333
I just don't want
Carrie to miss out on that.

24:26.333 --> 24:31.709
Because, you know, her dad
couldn't make a tough call.

24:35.500 --> 24:36.917
Let's do it.

24:36.917 --> 24:40.000
- Really?
- Yeah.

24:40.000 --> 24:44.333
- Let's do it.
Let's do the surgery.
- Thank you. Thank you.

24:53.834 --> 24:58.583
You all right?
Your face seems a little red.

24:58.583 --> 25:03.291
Oh, it's just hot in there.
You know, with the fire.

25:03.291 --> 25:07.542
Yeah, yeah. Well, actually,
I have a little trick for that.

25:12.709 --> 25:16.959
- You know why this works?
- Why?

25:16.959 --> 25:19.875
Because the vein in your
wrist is a major blood vessel.

25:19.875 --> 25:21.417
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

25:28.458 --> 25:30.417
What are we doing?

25:32.458 --> 25:33.834
I don't know.

25:36.291 --> 25:39.709
[Jimmy] Adam! Get in here.
Let's get Celebrity going again.

25:39.709 --> 25:42.667
All right.
Come on, we'll talk later.

25:45.583 --> 25:49.000
- I don't care.
- What's with the attitude?

25:49.000 --> 25:51.542
[chattering]

25:53.041 --> 25:55.458
- Hey.
- Hey.

26:12.166 --> 26:14.250
OK. What are we doing
out here again?

26:14.250 --> 26:16.750
- I said I wanted a cigarette.
- You don't smoke.

26:16.750 --> 26:18.542
They don't know that.

26:18.542 --> 26:22.166
- You lied to me!
- I never lied to you!

26:22.166 --> 26:24.375
Oh, this is all my fault.

26:24.375 --> 26:26.709
- No, it isn't.
- Yeah, it is.

26:26.709 --> 26:30.083
OK? Heather came to see me.
She told me to stay away
from Adam.

26:30.834 --> 26:31.959
It made me mad.

26:31.959 --> 26:35.041
Marjorie, he asked her
to come here.

26:35.041 --> 26:36.792
He invited her,
and she said no.

26:36.792 --> 26:39.667
We're old friends.
That's what this is about.

26:39.667 --> 26:41.458
You have every right
to be here.

26:41.458 --> 26:43.959
- I have cigarettes.
I'll go get them.
- No!

26:43.959 --> 26:47.625
Gotta give them their space.
Know what I don't understand?

26:47.625 --> 26:50.583
How come we're not inside
and they aren't out here?

26:50.583 --> 26:52.041
How could you
do this to me?

26:52.041 --> 26:54.375
If you didn't have that
stupid fight with Marjorie,

26:54.375 --> 26:56.250
she wouldn't have come!

26:56.250 --> 26:58.750
Why can't you see
that she is after you?

26:58.750 --> 27:03.125
She's playing a game, Adam.
With you and with me.

27:03.125 --> 27:05.667
All right, all right.
Let's just...

27:05.667 --> 27:08.500
Let's just cool down,
all right? Let's go for a walk.

27:08.500 --> 27:10.166
Adam.

27:13.166 --> 27:17.333
I want you to leave,
with me, right now.

27:17.333 --> 27:19.166
I don't want to leave.

27:19.166 --> 27:23.834
You know how important this
weekend is to me. These people
are my family.

27:23.834 --> 27:27.667
This is who I am. You can't ask
me to walk away from my friends.

27:27.667 --> 27:31.333
I'm only asking you
to walk away from one friend.

27:35.000 --> 27:36.208
Her.

27:38.667 --> 27:40.333
I'm not sure I can do that.

27:47.542 --> 27:50.500
[Ivy] Oh! Oh, oh, oh!
I think she's going to leave.

27:50.500 --> 27:51.959
Really?

27:51.959 --> 27:55.834
- Maybe it's meant for the best.
- She should have called first.

27:55.834 --> 28:00.166
- So it's her fault now?
- I didn't say that.

28:00.166 --> 28:03.542
God, what is wrong
with you people?

28:03.542 --> 28:06.792
You're like some
high school clique or something.

28:06.792 --> 28:11.667
God forbid someone new
comes in and you treat
them like a normal person.

28:11.667 --> 28:13.667
I'm new.

28:15.667 --> 28:20.000
OK. So maybe it's just me
you don't like.

28:22.417 --> 28:25.709
Bridget. [sighs]

28:25.709 --> 28:30.417
I say dump his ass.
And the rest of them too.

28:30.417 --> 28:34.750
- "Mansfield Park!"
- Shut up. Shut up. Come on.

28:36.375 --> 28:40.208
She's right.
You never gave her a chance.

28:43.917 --> 28:45.959
Don't listen
to anything she said.

28:48.792 --> 28:53.583
That girl left you at the altar.
I never would have done
that to you.

28:57.125 --> 28:59.166
You have a choice to make.

29:01.250 --> 29:02.792
Her or me.

29:06.166 --> 29:08.083
[exhales]

29:11.291 --> 29:16.291
[sobbing] I guess I fulfilled
all my own prophecies, huh?

29:16.291 --> 29:19.000
I was way too competitive,
I took the best bedroom,

29:19.000 --> 29:22.333
and now I'm
the crying girlfriend.

29:22.333 --> 29:24.500
Heather's crying too.

29:28.667 --> 29:30.667
What did they say
about me out there?

29:30.667 --> 29:33.792
They didn't say anything.
I told them to shut up.

29:37.792 --> 29:40.000
You did?

29:40.000 --> 29:43.250
- You're surprised?
- [panting]

29:44.333 --> 29:46.041
They're your people, Brian.

29:46.041 --> 29:50.458
You guys are really close.
I can see that.
But they are not rooting for us.

29:50.458 --> 29:54.375
We're not rooting for us.
We can't figure out who
gives up their apartment.

29:54.375 --> 29:56.875
We're not moving in together.

30:02.709 --> 30:04.542
Honey, yes, we are.

30:06.208 --> 30:08.500
They'll come around.

30:08.500 --> 30:14.166
And even if they don't...
I don't care.

30:14.166 --> 30:19.041
I'm always comparing myself
to them, to what they have.
And you know what?

30:20.709 --> 30:23.333
What we have
is pretty fantastic.

30:26.875 --> 30:31.208
You just called me honey.
That's the first time
you've ever done that.

30:31.208 --> 30:33.917
- Is it?
- Mm-hm.

30:39.208 --> 30:42.750
I really think I love you.

30:42.750 --> 30:45.542
I love you, Brian.

30:51.750 --> 30:53.583
I love you too.

31:01.625 --> 31:03.542
Jane Austen.

31:06.125 --> 31:08.875
[Jimmy] I just didn't think
it would come to this.

31:08.875 --> 31:12.291
I knew it would
happen all along.

31:12.291 --> 31:13.959
People need to be honest.

31:13.959 --> 31:17.417
You can't say what you
think the other wants to hear.
Say what you want.

31:17.417 --> 31:21.083
I don't know what goes on
between you two, but I think

31:21.083 --> 31:23.959
this is easier to figure out
than you're making it.

31:27.417 --> 31:29.000
Marjorie's right.

31:32.417 --> 31:35.458
Ivy, if you want a cat,
you should have a cat.

31:35.458 --> 31:37.583
- Oh!
- [applause and cheering]

31:37.583 --> 31:40.417
[all] Meow, meow, meow, meow.

31:40.417 --> 31:43.417
- Dave, I got the dip.
- [Dave] Oh.

31:43.417 --> 31:46.291
- [soft rock music plays]
- ♪ Trying to catch
my breath again ♪

31:46.291 --> 31:51.750
♪ One more time
you had me believing ♪

31:54.709 --> 31:57.375
♪ Everything you took from me ♪

31:57.375 --> 31:59.959
♪ To try to make your remedy ♪

31:59.959 --> 32:02.750
♪ You can't keep it ♪

32:04.542 --> 32:07.291
♪ Don't you want ♪

32:07.291 --> 32:09.875
♪ Don't you need ♪

32:09.875 --> 32:14.166
♪ To be forgiven? ♪

32:14.166 --> 32:17.166
♪ Do as you say not as you do ♪

32:17.166 --> 32:19.500
♪ Exciting conversations ♪

32:19.500 --> 32:22.834
♪ With no meaning ♪

32:25.625 --> 32:28.375
♪ Dress it up
or dress it down ♪

32:28.375 --> 32:30.917
♪ It's all the same
when you walk out ♪

32:30.917 --> 32:35.542
♪ Still leaving ♪

32:35.542 --> 32:38.250
♪ Don't you want ♪

32:38.250 --> 32:41.166
♪ Don't you need ♪

32:41.166 --> 32:43.709
♪ Something more ♪

32:43.709 --> 32:46.834
♪ To set you free? ♪

32:46.834 --> 32:49.667
♪ Don't you want ♪

32:49.667 --> 32:52.166
♪ Don't you need ♪

32:52.166 --> 32:55.792
♪ To be forgiven? ♪♪

33:23.709 --> 33:28.542
- How you doing?
- [scoffs] I don't know.

33:30.083 --> 33:34.041
Ever since that day that
Marjorie didn't show up
for the wedding,

33:34.041 --> 33:36.875
it's like I've been
living in this dream.

33:36.875 --> 33:40.208
And everything I've done
since then doesn't count.

33:40.208 --> 33:44.625
And I've been criticizing you
for not committing,

33:44.625 --> 33:47.166
but I haven't really
committed to Heather.

33:47.166 --> 33:49.417
I haven't really
given her a chance.

33:51.333 --> 33:54.041
- Last night, Marjorie and I...
- I know, I know.

33:54.041 --> 33:55.709
I saw her come out
of your room.

34:01.500 --> 34:05.750
[groans] Do people
think I'm an ass?

34:05.750 --> 34:08.458
